1 THE REGION WHERE THE APPLICANT LIVES; OR
2 3. A COMMUNITY COLLEGE IN THE STATE THAT HAS AN
3 ON–CAMPUS RESIDENTIAL FACILITY FOR STUDENTS; AND
4 (II) 1. Enrolls as a candidate for a vocational certificate, a
5 certificate, or an associate’s degree or participates in a registered apprenticeship after
6 graduating from a high school or successfully completing a GED in the State[:
7 (i) Except as provided in item (ii) of this item, at the community
8 college located in the county or, in the case of a regional community college, in the region,
9 where the applicant lives; or
10 (ii) At a community college in the State that has an on–campus
11 residential facility for students]; OR
12 2. A. ENROLLS AS A CANDIDATE FOR A VOCATIONAL
13 CERTIFICATE, A CERTIFICATE, OR AN ASSOCIATE’S DEGREE OR PARTICIPATES IN A
14 REGISTERED APPRENTICESHIP AFTER GRADUATING FROM DELMAR HIGH SCHOOL
15 IN DELMAR, DELAWARE; AND
16 B. IS A RESIDENT OF DELMAR, MARYLAND;
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
18 1, 2026.

